title: NETWORK ENGINEER
shortDescription: Design, Install and configure LAN, WAN management, Internet and network security and ...
description:
Design, Install and configure LAN, WAN management, Internet and network security and configuration of Cisco Catalyst switches 6500, 4000 and 3750 series and routers according to the Network Design.

Job Overview

Design, Install and configure LAN, WAN management, Internet and network security and configuration of Cisco Catalyst switches 6500, 4000 and 3750 series and routers according to the Network Design. Configured routing protocol OSPF, EIGRP, BGP. Configuring and implementing routing protocols such as RIP, OSPF and Static routing on Juniper M and MX series Router. Design and Implement network design using TCP/IP. Troubleshoot and technical support for Global wide area network consisting of Multi-Protocol label switching MPLS, VPN and point-to point site.

Education and Experience Requirements

Masters degree in Computer Science (any), Engineering (any), MBA (any) or alternatively a Bachelor’s degree (any) with 5 years of relevant experience in lieu of a Masters degree.
